Oceans Bible College Graduate 🤍 
May 30, 2023 | Year Three 🏁

Encountered and forever changed. There are not enough words to describe what these last three years have been @oceanscollege 

July 2020 Andrea @dre.rhodes asked me if I wanted to go with her to Bible College. At the time I didn’t know what Bible college was. In that moment I had such a peace to say yes without knowing anything about it and never having been to Oceans Church in faith I said yes. I applied the next day and then one month later we are moving our lives from LA to Orange County.

What an journey it has been. So many moments where God did deep work in my heart, set me free from false mindsets, met me time and time again, affirmed me as a daughter, showed Himself as a good good Father, broke off bondage and healed me from childhood trauma, set me free from fear of man crippling my voice, purified, renewed and redeemed my story, revealed purpose and my call, and the list goes on and on and on! I am now committed to this journey of saying yes to Him over and over and over again knowing that God is just getting started and this is just the beginning.

I forever hold thankfulness and gratefulness in my heart that God set me under the leadership of world class leaders who have sewed countless hours into me. My pastors are the real deal, ones who said yes to the call when it was hard, ones who are so obedient to Gods timing, one’s who walk in integrity and walk the walk they talk, live with high convictions, one’s who have taught me how to pray and hear the voice of the Lord! I am forever grateful to them for forging the path and pioneering this movement.

Forever grateful and thankful for my Pastor’s @markfrancey & @kenziepoo , @foustjoel & @melfoust , @chrismbristow , @wolfepa , @chloedelk , @stephaniedunson 🤍

October 🧡

To be effective intercessors we must be like watchmen on the wall. 

I have set watchmen on your walls, O Jerusalem; they shall never hold their peace day or night. You who make mention of the Lord, do not keep silent, and give Him no rest till He establishes and till he makes Jerusalem a praise in the earth ~ Isaiah 62:6-7

Jerusalem is a walled city, and you can still walk on the top of these walls. Watchmen used to walk up and down them, peer into the night and guard against potential attacks of the enemy upon the city. God is telling us today to look into the distance through prayer to see potential harm that may come to our cities, churches or families. God is establishing His people as watchmen to give Him no rest until the Kingdom of God is established throughout the world.

I love it here @oceanschurch & everyone in it 🤍
